- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with algorithms for computing roots of polynomials. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses randomized and deterministic algorithms for polynomial computations. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the polynomial-time complexity of the algorithms. 
- cs.NT (Number Theory) is relevant as the paper relies on a number-theoretic conjecture for one of the algorithms. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the structure of polynomials in the lacunary representation.
